The paper deals with resource allocation and optimization in an edge computing environment, which involves multiple servers and clients. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization and algorithm design, which could place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also formulates the problem as a stochastic optimization problem, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The paper uses techniques such as decomposition and Lyapunov optimization, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Finally, the paper deals with maximizing service capacity, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
